sub_topic: The Hausdorff dimension of the Vicsek fractal.
message_1: What is the Hausdorff dimension of the Vicsek fractal at the 5th iteration?
message_2:
The Hausdorff dimension of the Vicsek fractal can be found using the formula:

D = log(N) / log(s)

where D is the Hausdorff dimension, N is the number of self-similar pieces, and s is the scaling factor.

For the Vicsek fractal, N = 5 (since there are 5 smaller copies of the fractal in each iteration), and the scaling factor s = 3 (as each side of the square is divided into 3 equal parts).

So, the Hausdorff dimension of the Vicsek fractal is:

D = log(5) / log(3)

The Hausdorff dimension remains constant for all iterations of the fractal, so the dimension at the 5th iteration is also approximately 1.465.
